description:
Japanese title: Orenji-iro no Kagayaki (オレンジ色の輝き)

Inside his mind, Naruto continues his battle against Nine Tails to take control of its immense power.
name: The Orange Spark

description:
Japanese title: Nerawareta Kyūbi (狙われた九尾)

Sixteen years ago, Fourth Hokage Minato Namikaze and his wife Kushina are expecting their first child, much to the delight of the young couple.
name: Target: Nine Tails

description:
Japanese title: Yondaime no Shitō!! (四代目の死闘!!)

Minato is forced to use his Flying Raijin jutsu and leave his wife Kushina behind to save their newborn son, Naruto, from a masked assailant.
name: The Fourth Hokage's Death Match!

description:
Japanese title: Arigatō (「ありがとう」)

Minato uses his Transportation Technique to move Nine Tails away from the Hidden Leaf Village.
name: Thank You

description:
Japanese title: Chinjū VS Kaijin! Rakuen no Tatakai! (珍獣VS怪人! 楽園の戦い!)

Guy arrives at the Waterfall of Truth to help Naruto with his training. Instead he encounters Kisame, who has infiltrated the island to locate Naruto and Killer Bee.
name: Battle in Paradise! Odd Beast vs. The Monster!

description:
Japanese title: Kisame to Iu Otoko (鬼鮫という男)

Kisame’s escape is prevented thanks to Guy’s efforts. Aoba enters Kisame’s mind to gather intel on the Akatsuki.
name: The Man Named Kisame

description:
Japanese title: Shi e Izanau Tenshi (死へいざなう天使)

Madara appears in the Hidden Rain Village seeking the corpse of Nagato and his Rinnegan.
name: The Angelic Herald of Death

description:
Japanese title: Heiwa e no Kakehashi (平和への懸け橋)

Madara uses the forbidden jutsu Izanagi to escape Konan’s Paper Bomb trap.
name: The Bridge to Peace

description:
Japanese title: Doesu-kyū Gokuhi Ninmu (ドS級極秘任務)

The Leaf and Cloud ninja prepare to relocate Naruto and Bee, as the Akatsuki may already have knowledge of their location.
name: The Super Secret S-Rank Mission

first_appearance_objects.name: Demonic Statue of the Outer Path

object_credits.name: Demonic Statue of the Outer Path

description:
Japanese title: Geijutsuka Futatabi (芸術家再び)

Kabuto and a reanimated Deidara attempt to grab hold of the jinchuriki, but are stopped by the Tsuchikage.
name: The Artist Returns

deck: A new teen finds his own Energem and joins Tyler and Shelby on their pilgrimage to the Amber Beach Dinosaur Museum, where they learn they are a part of the elite team called the Power Rangers. They are entrusted with protecting the Energems from a fierce bounty hunter named Sledge, who has returned and is more determined than ever to capture the Energems for himself.
name: Past, Present and Fusion

description:
Japanese title: Shūketsu! Shinobi Rengōgun! (集結! 忍連合軍!)

The Tsuchikage and his team manage to safeguard the Jinchuriki, but at the cost of losing Yamato to the enemy.
name: Assemble! Allied Shinobi Forces!

description:
Japanese title: Kazoku no Shōzō (家族の肖像)

As Raven tries to corrupt Armstrong, Ed and Al can only wait in their cell. Long ago, their father faced his own captivity, confined to an eternity of regret in an undying body. To escape the pain, he said goodbye.
name: Family Portrait

description:
Japanese title: Hajimari no Homunkurusu (始まりの人造人間（ホムンクルス）)

Hawkeye is shocked when the first Homunculus reveals itself. Far away, Edward is surprised by an offer from Kimblee: Fullmetal can have all he has searched for - in exchange for becoming a mass murderer.
name: The First Homunculus

description:
Japanese title: Bazukūru no Gekitō (バズクールの激闘)

When Scar is cornered by a pair of gruesome chimeras, the Elrics enter the fray as his unlikely allies. Later, Winry’s attempt to confront Scar over his role in her parent’s death ends in disaster.
name: Conflict at Baschool

description:
Japanese title: Hakuchū no Yume (白昼の夢)

The ruse of Winry’s abduction by Scar is revealed, but a plan of rescue must still be hatched. A brutal storm is coming - one which only Alphonse Elric can brave.
name: Daydream

description:
Japanese title: Homunkurusu (フラスコの中の小人)

Long ago, the blood of a simple slave was used in an experiment which created a strange, shapeless being. In exchange for the gift of existence, the being gave the slave a name - and cursed him with immortality.
name: (Homunculus) The Dwarf in the Flask

description:
Japanese title: Naraku (奈落)

Bound by more than blood, the Elrics have long shared joy and pain. Now, with Al wandering the frigid void - and Ed losing blood by Kimblee’s hand - the mystical connection of their souls could prove fatal.
name: The Abyss

description:
Japanese title: Hangeki no Kizashi (反撃の兆し)

May and Marcoh’s efforts to decode the research of Scar’s brother yield progress, but it might be too late to prevent catastrophe. Violence is spreading across the land, and it will soon reach the northern border.
name: Signs of a Counter Offensive

description:
Japanese title: Ari no Hito Kami (蟻のひと噛み)

In the snowy north, the soldiers of Fort Briggs engage an invading army, and Marcoh leads an attack against monstrous Envy. In Central, an ominous and shocking secret is revealed to Olivier Armstrong.
name: Bite of the Ant

description:
Japanese title: Barinbarin no Zenkai (バリンバリンの全開)

Hohenheim and Alphonse enjoy a chance to get reacquainted. Their bond is restored with ease, inspiring the father to share his secrets with his sons - but one of them is far away and on the run.
name: Revving at Full-throttle

description:
Japanese title: Yakusoku no Hi (約束の日)

Quiet warnings spread near and far: the Promised Day is at hand. While most will face the coming chaos with their own kind, Edward forms a new cabal comprised of human, chimera - and Homunculus.
name: The Promised Day
Rise Up, Oh Dregs of Humanity

description:
Japanese title: Semaru Kage (迫る影)

Those who have prepared to reclaim a nation find their plans exposed. The chaos multiplies after an assassin strikes down a mighty leader in broad daylight, and Alphonse falls prey to monsters in the dark.
name: Looming Shadows

description:
Japanese title: Yami no Shisha (闇の使者)

A sinister voice rings out from the shell of Al’s armor, and Ed and Greed find themselves under attack. As the Homunculi use the darkness to their advantage, a face from the past arrives to join the battle.
name: Emissary of Darkness
Twilight of the Papers, Part I

description:
Japanese title: Chikadō no Chikai (地下道の誓い)

After investigating the twisted roots of the Bradley family tree, Mustang gathers his most loyal troops. Meanwhile, Ed and his allies continue fighting Selim, who shocks everyone by turning on his own kind.
name: The Oath in the Tunnel
Twilight of the Papers, Part II
Forest of Paper Leaves (or "Paper Leaf Wood")
In the Gray Light of the Abyss

description:
Japanese title: Oyako no Jō (親子の情)

With his father’s help, Al takes incredible steps to contain the monstrous Pride. As the sun begins to rise on the Promised Day, the youngest Elric listens while the Homunculus ponders his very human mother.
name: Filial Affection

description:
Japanese title: Sentoraru Dōran (セントラル動乱)

Mustang leads a ragtag assault force of hardy northern troops - and welcome faces from the past - against Central’s defenses. Victory seems certain until the military’s most horrifying secret is revealed.
name: Upheaval in Central

description:
Japanese title: Fushi no Gundan (不死の軍団)

Ed’s crew faces a horde of ravenous mannequins, abominations powered by human souls. The twisted creatures aren't the only unstoppable force on the battlefield -Pride, Sloth, and Envy are on the move.
name: The Immortal Legion

description:
Japanese title: Minna no Chikara (みんなの力)

With a Philosopher’s Stone in his possession, Alphonse fearlessly engages Pride and Kimblee. Elsewhere, the Armstrongs find themselves trapped between Sloth’s onslaught and the guns of Central’s troops.
name: Combined Strength

description:
Japanese title: Fukushū no Honō (復讐の炎)

After a startling radio broadcast grants Mustang’s forces the advantage over Central’s troops, the Flame Alchemist unleashes the brutal power of burning hatred in the battle against the killer of Maes Hughes.
name: Flame of Vengeance

description:
Japanese title: Rekka no Saki ni (烈火の先に)

As Envy writhes within the firestorm unleashed by Mustang’s vengeful rage, Hawkeye must take drastic measures to prevent the Flame Alchemist’s hatred from burning out of control.
name: Beyond the Inferno

description:
Japanese title: Otona-tachi no Ikizama (大人たちの生き様)

A rebel victory is imminent and hope takes hold among Mustang and Armstrong’s troops. Central’s forces teeter on the brink of collapse - until their fallen leader returns to take control.
name: The Adults' Way of Life

description:
Japanese title: Daisōtō no Kikan (大総統の帰還)

Central’s forces fight with renewed vigor following Bradley’s return, and the Fuhrer himself enters the battle. His first opponent is an armored tank. His second foe is even tougher.
name: The Return of the Fuhrer

description:
Japanese title: Eien no Itoma (永遠の暇)

The battle for a nation’s soul descends into chaos. Bradley unleashes death on those who dare engage him. Beneath Central, the one responsible for the Fuhrer’s creation unleashes something far, far worse.
name: Eternal Leave

description:
Japanese title: Hitobashira (ひとばしら)

Mustang must make a difficult choice: will he break alchemy’s greatest taboo? Or will he watch the person dearest to him die? Meanwhile, it grows ever more difficult to discern where Ling ends and Greed begins.
name: Sacrifices

description:
Japanese title: Ushinawareta Hikari (失われた光)

As the light of the sun vanishes, Mustang learns the loss which comes from seeing the other side of the Gateway - and five sacrifices gather in the dark presence of the Father.
name: Lost Light

description:
Japanese title: Ten no Hitomi, Chi no Tobira (天の瞳、地の扉)

The light is gone. Shadows swallow everything. As the planet quakes and the heavens tremble, the souls of heroes and villains alike vanish into darkness. The circle is complete.
name: Eye of Heaven, Gateway of Earth

description:
Japanese title: Kami o Nomikomishi Mono (神を呑みこみし者)

Millions of lifeless bodies litter the landscape of Amestris, and a being with the power to create suns is unleashed upon the world. Unless Hohenheim has something amazing up his sleeve, all is surely lost.
name: He Who would Swallow God

description:
Japanese title: Seizetsunaru Hangeki (凄絶なる反撃)

A truly epic battle erupts when Edward, Mustang, Hawkeye, Greed, Izumi, and Armstrong attack the god-like Father. The odds are against the forces of good - until one brave boy makes a shocking sacrifice.
name: A Fierce Counterattack

description:
Japanese title: Tobira no Mukōgawa (扉の向こう側)

When the battle ends, the one known as Father meets his final fate beyond the Gateway. When the one known as Fullmetal enters the sacred space, he finds only the promise of a new beginning.
name: The Other Side of the Gateway

description: Gordon takes Dr. Leslie Thompkins to the circus, but the day turns quickly when the circus comes under attack. Then, Falcone enlists Butch Gilzean to help Penguin with the night club, while Fish Mooney is otherwise occupied. Also, Bruce Wayne schedules a meeting with the Wayne Enterprises board.
name: The Blind Fortune Teller

description: Cyborg asks Raven to make him a real boy again.
name: Real Boy Adventures

description:
Japanese title: Tabiji no Hate (旅路の涯)

As one shared journey ends, many journeys begin. Those most touched by the conflict which surrounded the Philosopher’s Stone now go their separate ways. One thing is certain: they will meet again.
name: Journey's End

description: Lemongrab and Finn go on a journey of discovery through the Mountain of Matthew.
name: The Mountain

description: Susan Strong and her allies infiltrate the mysterious Super Porp factory.
name: Dark Purple

description: The Discmasters have to end the Format Wars once and for all.
name: Format Wars II

description: Following several bank robberies, Gordon and Bullock investigate the Red Hood gang. Selina Kyle continues to bond with Barbara, and Fish Mooney tries to reclaim her position in the underworld.
name: Red Hood

description: After the nuclear explosion separates Ronnie (guest star Robbie Amell) and Dr. Stein (guest star Victor Garber), Barry (Grant Gustin) and the team believe both men are safe. Caitlin (Danielle Panabaker) is thrilled to have her fiancé back and prepares to resume their life together while Dr. Stein returns to his wife. However, when General Eiling (guest star Clancy Brown) targets Firestorm, Ronnie and Dr. Stein must decide if they are safer together or apart. Meanwhile, Mason Bridge (guest star Roger Hayworth) tells Iris (Candice Patton) that there is something secretive going on at S.T.A.R. Labs and Dr. Stein gives Barry some important information about time travel.
name: Fallout

description: Brian accompanies Stewie on an open-road adventure when Stewie decides he wants to experience life outside of preschool. Meanwhile, Meg is thrilled to be recruited as a model.
name: This Little Piggy

description: Peter discovers that his first name is actually Justin, which he adopts as the name of his younger "bro"-style alter-ego.
name: Quagmire's Mom

description: Peter, Quagmire, Joe and Cleveland form a neighborhood detective agency, and are stunned to discover that Chris is a thief. Meanwhile, Lois is worried about Chris' delusional relationship with his new girlfriend, but also sees it as an opportunity for Peter to copy Chris' romantic gestures.
name: Encyclopedia Griffin

description:
Japanese title: Momoku no Renkinjutsushi (盲目の錬金術師)

Ed and Al seek out an alchemist named Judeau after hearing rumors that he successfully completed a human transmutation. The Elrics find him in the service of a wealthy household and quickly become tangled in a web of family secrets and disturbing lies.
name: The Blind Alchemist

description:
Japanes title: Shinpuru na Hitobito (シンプルな人々)

Winry and Hawkeye couldn’t be more different. One is a bright-eyed youth, the other a hardened soldier. Still, common ground exists - in a world full of pain, both take the time to appreciate the little things in life that make them who they are.
name: Simple People

description:
Japanese title: Sensei Monogatari (師匠物語)

18 year-old Izumi travels north to ask a famous alchemist, Silver Steiner, if she can study as his apprentice. The crotchety old man is willing to give her a shot - if she can survive for one month in the hostile wilds of the Briggs mountain range.
name: The Tale of Teacher

description:
Japanese title: Sore mo Mata Kare no Senjō (それもまた彼の戦場)

Before they were best friends and officers, Roy Mustang and Maes Hughes were military school rivals. When they finally settled their differences, they swore to never compromise their ideals. Unfortunately, ideals are often the first casualties of war.
name: Yet Another Man's Battlefield

description:
Original English and Japanese title:

English: The Mightiest Warrior in All of History is Goku's Older Brother!

Japanese: Shijō Saikyō no Senshi wa Gokū no Ani Datta! (史上最強の戦士は悟空の兄だった！)

Goku and Gohan attend a reunion on Master Roshi’s island, where Goku introduces his son to all of his old friends. The smiles quickly fade, however, as an unexpected visitor - Raditz - lands on the island.
name: Reunions

description:
Original English and Japanese titles:

English: All Right! This is the Strongest Combo in the World!

Japanese: Yatta! Kore ga Chijō Saikyō no Konbi Da! (やった！これが地上最強のコンビだ！)

Raditz has kidnapped Gohan, and unless Goku agrees to join the sinister Saiyan, he may never see his son again! All hope is not lost, however, as a second visitor arrives, and Goku forges an unlikely alliance!
name: Unlikely Alliance

description:
Original English and Japanese title:

English: Piccolo's Trump Card! Gohan, the Crybaby-kun.

Japanese: Pikkoro no Kirifuda! Gohan wa Nakimushikun (ピッコロの切り札！悟飯は泣きむしクン)

Piccolo may have a way to stop Raditz - the Special Beam Cannon! There’s only one problem. He needs time to gather energy for the blast, which means Goku must fight Raditz alone!
name: Piccolo's Plan
